content: User added further context for their work at OJCommerce: The primary driver of growth from $30M to $100M in 3 years was vendor onboarding, which included identifying and scoring targets, outreach, value propositions, negotiations, and contract closure. They led the development of an AI/ML algorithm to score targets based on aggregated reviews and retail prices, automating parts of the sales process to manage high volumes. The category expansion efforts involved AI/ML initiatives for mapping features and attributes, such as color mapping. They also developed AI/ML algorithms for compliance, proactively identifying potential issues.
